          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The gamma-ray    spectra    from    the     reactions",
                " S-32(gamma,p+gamma')P-31                         and",
                " S-32(gamma,n+gamma')S-31 have been measured by means",
                " of   a   100-cm**3  Ge(Li)  detector;  the  incident",
                " gamma-quanta were from the bremsstrahlung beam  with",
                " a  end-point  energy of 32 MeV.  The detection angle",
                " was 140 degrees.  The partial angle dependent  cross",
                " section  integrals  were obtained for the population",
                " of separate states of  the  final  nuclei  P-31  and",
                " S-31.  On  the  basis  of  the  isospin  symmetry of",
                " nucleon decays the partial  and  total  photoneutron",
                " cross  sections  of  the  nucleus S-32 were obtained",
                " from the experimental data on the energy  dependence",
                " of   the   partial   photoproton   cross   sections.",
                " Semi-direct  components  were  singled  out  in  the",
                " photoproton  and  photoneutron  cross sections.  The",
                " photoabsorption cross sections  of  S-32  were  also",
                " extracted  and  the  probabilities of the semidirect",
                " mechanism are determined for the decay of the dipole",
                " giant   resonance   in   the   nucleus   to  various",
                " photodisintegration channels."
              ]
            }
          ],
